      - codedna-plugin/commands/check.md
      - codedna-plugin/commands/impact.md
      - codedna-plugin/.claude-plugin/plugin.json
      - QUICKSTART.md
    message: >
      Added cmd_self_update() + 'self-update' subcommand. Resolves a UX confusion:
      users seeing 'codedna update' thought it upgraded the package, but it just
      annotates new files. Now 'codedna update' keeps its annotation meaning and
      'codedna self-update' is the dedicated upgrade path. Implementation uses
      sys.executable -m pip so the upgrade always targets the same Python that is
      running the CLI. Detects editable/dev checkouts (pyproject.toml + .git
      present in package parent) and refuses pip --force-reinstall unless --force
      is explicitly passed — prevents clobbering dev environments. --check shows
      installed version without running pip. Tested in a clean venv: editable
      detection works, pip is invoked correctly with the right interpreter, the
      remote install actually replaces the local package. Plugin-side wiki.md
      command was started but reverted on user request — they prefer keeping the
      wiki layer CLI-only for now.

